| Busting the MythBusters' Yawn Experiment                           |
|   from the it's-not-the-company-it's-the-hour dept.                |
|   posted by kdawson on Monday April 23, @21:22 (Math)              |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/23/2218246      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]markmcb writes "Most everyone knows and loves the MythBusters, two
guys who attempt to set the story straight on things people just take for
granted. Well, maybe everyone except Brandon Hansen, who has offered them
a taste of their own medicine as he [1]busts the MythBusters' improper
use of statistics in their experiment to determine whether yawning is
contagious. While the article maintains that the contagion of yawns is
still a possibility, Hansen is clearly giving the MythBusters no credit
for proving such a claim, 'not with a correlation coefficient of
.045835.'"

