of EU requests by asking [0]how much the EU thinks they should charge for
Windows Server Protocols. The EU has stated the Microsoft should charge
based on 'innovation, not patentability' and that they have 'examined 160
Microsoft claims to patented technologies' concluding 'only four may only
deserve to claim a limited degree of innovation.' The EU is also starting
to discuss structural remedies as opposed to the behavioral remedies they
are currently enforcing. At what point has/will the EU overstepped its
bounds?"

