+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Next-Gen Processor Unveiled                                        |
|   from the trillions-and-trillions dept.                           |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday April 24, @16:33 (Supercomputing)   |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/24/2021243     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

A bunch of readers sent us word on the prototype for a [0]new
general-purpose processor with the potential of reaching trillions of
calculations per second. TRIPS (obligatory back-formation given in the
article) was designed and built by a team at the University of Texas at
Austin. The TRIPS chip is a demonstration of a new class of processing
architectures called Explicit Data Graph Execution. Each TRIPS contains
two processing cores, each of which can issue 16 operations per cycle
with up to 1,024 instructions in flight simultaneously. The article
claims that current high-performance processors typically are designed to
sustain a maximum execution rate of four operations per cycle.

Discuss this story at:
    http://hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/24/2021243

Links:
    0. http://www.scienceblog.com/cms/next-generation-high-performance-processor-unveiled-13080.html


